br /><br /><b>
  <i>So I prepared two answers – one that is polite but kind of wordy, and one that is a little smart-mouthed. To those who are genuinely concerned, I push a button to say, “I have spastic bilateral quadriplegia, also known as cerebral palsy. It limits my body, not my mind” I think that last part is pretty cool. To people like Claire and Molly, I say, "We all have disabilities. What's yours?"<br /><br /><br />“What would you do if you could fly?” Mrs. V asks…<br />“I’d be scared to let go,” I type.<br />“Afraid you’d fall?” she asks.<br />“No. Afraid it would feel so good, I’d just fly away”. It took me a long time to type that.</i>
